01:28:48,824 --> 01:28:50,406
"It was an accident."

1544
01:28:50,534 --> 01:28:52,241
The two men had quarreled

1545
01:28:52,369 --> 01:28:54,452
over Drollet's treatment
of Cheyenne Brando.

1546
01:28:54,579 --> 01:28:58,368
Mistreatment police say allegedly
included physical beating.

1547
01:28:58,500 --> 01:29:01,789
"Two guys with a loaded gun, wrestling."

1548
01:29:02,420 --> 01:29:04,833
"It goes off and he's dead."

1549
01:29:08,635 --> 01:29:10,877
I saw Dag laying there

1550
01:29:11,847 --> 01:29:14,681
and I breathed into his mouth

1551
01:29:14,808 --> 01:29:16,720
and I called 911.

1552
01:29:18,186 --> 01:29:20,143
Asking leniency for his son,

1553
01:29:20,272 --> 01:29:24,812
Brando said Christian's life had been
filled with struggle and unhappiness,

1554
01:29:24,943 --> 01:29:27,856
traumatized by a bitter divorce.

1555
01:29:27,988 --> 01:29:30,446
I think that
perhaps I failed as a father.

1556
01:29:30,615 --> 01:29:33,699
And certainly there were things
that I could've done differently,

1557
01:29:33,827 --> 01:29:35,489
had I known better at the time.

1558
01:29:35,620 --> 01:29:37,452
I am at fault in this.

1559
01:29:37,581 --> 01:29:41,325
And if I could trade places with Dag,
I would.

1560
01:29:41,459 --> 01:29:45,294
The total sentence imposed
is ten years in the state prison.

1561
01:29:46,590 --> 01:29:50,174
Cheyenne Brando is suffering
from mental and physical problems

1562
01:29:50,385 --> 01:29:53,128
and cannot travel here
to testify about what she knows.

1563
01:29:53,263 --> 01:29:55,550
Cheyenne is doing her best...

1564
01:29:59,895 --> 01:30:02,638
Excuse me... sorry.

1565
01:30:03,440 --> 01:30:06,524
Another personal tragedy
for actor Marlon Brando.

1566
01:30:06,651 --> 01:30:09,064
His 25-year-old daughter Cheyenne

1567
01:30:09,195 --> 01:30:11,562
has committed suicide at her home
in Tahiti.

1568
01:30:11,698 --> 01:30:14,782
Cheyenne Brando reportedly
had made several suicide attempts

1569
01:30:14,910 --> 01:30:17,072
before hanging herself yesterday.

1570
01:30:18,830 --> 01:30:20,196
For Marlon Brando,

1571
01:30:20,332 --> 01:30:24,076
Tahiti will never quite be
the same again.

1572
01:30:39,184 --> 01:30:43,224
When in disgrace
with fortune and men's eyes,

1573
01:30:43,355 --> 01:30:46,063
I all alone beweep my outcast state,

1574
01:30:46,191 --> 01:30:47,807
and trouble deaf heaven

1575
01:30:47,943 --> 01:30:50,276
with my bootless cries,

1576
01:30:50,445 --> 01:30:53,779
and look upon myself and curse my fate.

1577
01:31:04,292 --> 01:31:06,909
There are times
when you wake up in the morning

1578
01:31:07,045 --> 01:31:10,664
and you turn over and feel,
"Shit! What a life."

1579
01:31:13,593 --> 01:31:15,334
God, I can't figure it out.

1580
01:31:15,512 --> 01:31:17,128
Why did it have to be this way?

1581
01:31:19,599 --> 01:31:20,965
I've had a hard year.

1582
01:31:22,727 --> 01:31:25,686
Maybe harder
than you could possibly imagine.

1583
01:31:31,903 --> 01:31:35,943
You try to be as strong as you can be,

1584
01:31:36,074 --> 01:31:39,943
but everybody reaches break point
sooner or later.

1585
01:31:42,080 --> 01:31:45,573
Pain - I knew I had to deal with it.

1586
01:31:47,002 --> 01:31:53,169
I've spent thousands upon thousands
of dollars on psychoanalysts

1587
01:31:53,299 --> 01:31:56,883
and those guys do absolutely nothing

1588
01:31:57,012 --> 01:32:01,006
but stick pliers and screwdrivers
in your brain.

1589
01:32:03,226 --> 01:32:05,889
Life will have given me the truth

1590
01:32:06,021 --> 01:32:08,183
and taken in exchange

1591
01:32:08,314 --> 01:32:10,226
what's left of my youth.

1592
01:32:12,068 --> 01:32:14,355
It took me a while to realize,

1593
01:32:14,529 --> 01:32:16,816
you gotta be your own analyst.

1594
01:32:18,825 --> 01:32:20,782
Unless we look inwards,

1595
01:32:20,910 --> 01:32:24,950
we will not ever be able
to clearly see outwards.

1596
01:32:26,791 --> 01:32:29,283
Nobody is born evil.

1597
01:32:29,419 --> 01:32:33,459
Most people are simply
getting over bad emotional habits

1598
01:32:33,631 --> 01:32:36,920
established in the first ten years
of their life.

1599
01:32:40,055 --> 01:32:44,390
Christian was burdened
with emotional disorders

1600
01:32:44,601 --> 01:32:47,389
and psychological disarray.

1601
01:32:47,562 --> 01:32:50,054
The kind of trouble that I had in life.

1602
01:32:53,068 --> 01:32:55,606
I never tried to be like my father,

1603
01:32:55,737 --> 01:32:58,480
but one inadvertently takes on

1604
01:32:58,656 --> 01:33:01,569
the characteristics of one's parents.

1605
01:33:03,328 --> 01:33:05,240
When my father died,

1606
01:33:05,413 --> 01:33:07,996
I imagined that he was slump-shouldered,

1607
01:33:08,124 --> 01:33:11,492
walking to the edge of eternity.

1608
01:33:11,711 --> 01:33:13,828
He looked back and said,

1609
01:33:13,963 --> 01:33:15,875
"I did the best I could, kid."

1610
01:33:17,717 --> 01:33:19,458
Finally I forgave my father,

1611
01:33:19,636 --> 01:33:24,256
because I realized
that I was a sinner because of him.

1612
01:33:24,390 --> 01:33:25,631
But he was a sinner,

1613
01:33:25,767 --> 01:33:28,305
because his mother left him
when he was four.

1614
01:33:28,436 --> 01:33:30,052
He didn't have a chance.

1615
01:33:32,774 --> 01:33:35,733
And through introspection

1616
01:33:35,860 --> 01:33:38,227
and the examination of my mind,

1617
01:33:38,363 --> 01:33:40,480
I feel as though I'm coming closer

1618
01:33:40,657 --> 01:33:42,523
to the common denominator

1619
01:33:42,700 --> 01:33:44,737
of what it means to be human.

1620
01:33:49,499 --> 01:33:52,663
Everybody is capable of hatred,

1621
01:33:52,794 --> 01:33:55,207
everybody is capable of love.

1622
01:33:55,380 --> 01:33:58,373
If we stretched ourselves
one way or another,

1623
01:33:58,550 --> 01:34:00,041
we could become murderers

1624
01:34:00,176 --> 01:34:02,088
or we could become saints.

1625
01:34:03,555 --> 01:34:05,547
I've done a lot of meditation.

1626
01:34:05,723 --> 01:34:09,012
The result is that
I have felt much calmer

1627
01:34:09,144 --> 01:34:12,808
and I've had moments
of real tranquility.

1628
01:34:14,149 --> 01:34:18,359
Don't you realize that you're thought of
as the greatest actor ever?

1629
01:34:18,486 --> 01:34:20,694
Tim's the greatest actor ever.

1630
01:34:20,822 --> 01:34:23,940
He pretends he loves me when he wants
something to eat. Get outta here.

1631
01:34:25,368 --> 01:34:29,112
Many times
I remember being down in the dumps

1632
01:34:29,247 --> 01:34:31,034
and then I saw a movie

1633
01:34:31,166 --> 01:34:34,125
that took me away for a few hours

1634
01:34:34,252 --> 01:34:36,744
and I was completely restored.

1635
01:34:38,590 --> 01:34:40,798
And I realized, oddly enough,

1636
01:34:40,925 --> 01:34:43,918
that actors make a contribution
to people's lives,

1637
01:34:44,053 --> 01:34:47,091
giving us a gift that you can't buy.

1638
01:34:48,016 --> 01:34:50,474
Something that they can imbue

1639
01:34:50,685 --> 01:34:52,927
with power and beauty and magnificence.

1640
01:34:53,062 --> 01:34:55,054
Something beyond themselves

1641
01:34:55,190 --> 01:34:56,977
and we do need that.

1642
01:34:58,568 --> 01:35:02,061
Acting is just making stuff up,

1643
01:35:02,197 --> 01:35:03,688
but that's okay.

1644
01:35:03,823 --> 01:35:05,610
Life is a rehearsal,

1645
01:35:05,742 --> 01:35:07,324
life is an improvisation.

1646
01:35:08,786 --> 01:35:12,245
I'm gonna have a special microphone
placed in my coffin,

1647
01:35:12,373 --> 01:35:14,865
so that when I wake up in there,

1648
01:35:15,001 --> 01:35:16,333
six feet under the ground,

1649
01:35:16,461 --> 01:35:19,124
I'm gonna say, "Do it differently."

1650
01:35:23,593 --> 01:35:27,052
Anthony. Come here, come here.

1651
01:35:29,432 --> 01:35:31,173
The death scene.

1652
01:35:31,309 --> 01:35:32,971
That's a tough scene to play.

1653
01:35:34,896 --> 01:35:38,765
You have to make them believe
that you're dying.

1654
01:35:38,900 --> 01:35:42,109
I would hope it would be
with one person.

1655
01:35:42,237 --> 01:35:44,103
It would be something simple,

1656
01:35:44,239 --> 01:35:46,606
like playing tiddlywinks

1657
01:35:46,783 --> 01:35:50,117
or... I don't know, jackstraws.

1658
01:35:54,332 --> 01:35:56,665
Oh, no!

1659
01:36:01,381 --> 01:36:04,044
Try to think
of the most intimate moment

1660
01:36:04,175 --> 01:36:06,167
that you've ever had in your life.

1661
01:36:07,637 --> 01:36:09,629
Run down in there. Run in there.

1662
01:36:11,099 --> 01:36:12,465
Where are you?

1663
01:36:39,877 --> 01:36:43,621
Marlon. Listen to my voice.

1664
01:36:44,674 --> 01:36:46,791
Just let go.

1665
01:36:47,719 --> 01:36:49,506
Just letting go.

1666
01:36:50,888 --> 01:36:52,379
Drift.

1667
01:36:52,515 --> 01:36:55,428
Drift like a cloud in the sky.

1668
01:36:57,603 --> 01:37:00,641
Drifting into that special state,

1669
01:37:00,815 --> 01:37:02,147
the state of peace

1670
01:37:02,275 --> 01:37:04,938
of the boy that you remember,

1671
01:37:05,069 --> 01:37:07,152
watching the elm leaves come down.

1672
01:37:13,202 --> 01:37:15,660
Don't hang on to thoughts,

1673
01:37:15,830 --> 01:37:17,742
don't hang on to anything.

1674
01:37:19,751 --> 01:37:22,038
They're old tapes,

1675
01:37:22,170 --> 01:37:23,877
no longer usable,

1676
01:37:24,047 --> 01:37:25,333
no longer useful.

1677
01:37:26,924 --> 01:37:28,631
Chuck 'em.

1678
01:37:28,760 --> 01:37:31,628
Put 'em aside. You don't need 'em.

1679
01:37:33,431 --> 01:37:36,674
You're there, you have arrived.

1680
01:37:39,562 --> 01:37:43,852
Your mind is becoming quieter
and quieter.

1681
01:37:44,859 --> 01:37:48,023
Bliss is coming over you...

1682
01:37:50,406 --> 01:37:51,772
Now.

1683
01:37:53,201 --> 01:37:54,988
Until the next time.

1684
01:37:59,165 --> 01:38:00,952
Sleep.

